{"TopicId":168054,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Accurate Rotating Parts","CreatedByName":"Knayder","CreatedById":183167,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T16:50:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Knayder","CreatedById":183167,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T16:50:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello, I\u0027m new KSP user, and I\u0027m creating A-10 plane. But I\u0027m not satisfied with only visual aspects. I want to make this plane nice to fly, and nice looking. To accomplish that task, I wanted to set vectors of thrust and aerodynamic on the same direction. To do it, I was adjusting angle of horizontal stabilizer (To compensate height of engines).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/L1VBdoS.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022L1VBdoS.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you can see on the picture, I can\u0027t get them on exactly the same direction.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo my question is I am able to set rotation value by typing it in some field? By mouse, I will never have such a precision :|\u003Cbr\u003E\nI was trying to find addon, but I didn\u0027t see any for the newset KSP version :\\\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T17:34:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPart Angle Display is what you are looking for; it\u00A0has been unofficially recompiled for 1.3.1 by linuxgurugamer (see the last post in the thread).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5773971269\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/73551-12x-part-angle-display-including-seamless-highly-accurate-rotation-v0324/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3189839\u0026amp;embedComment=3189839\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:246px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbalfreak","CreatedById":181766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T17:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7716678890\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127378-131-editor-extensions-redux-released-with-selectroot-merge-stripsymmetry-nooffsetlimits/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Anyway, I don\u0027t see any problem in the picture. You should take a better look at how the center of thrust interacts with the center of mass, wet and dry. With enough control surfaces minor misalignments are not a problem, and with RW and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E in vacuum.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMany players lose the control of the aircraft after spending some fuel and don\u0027t have a clue what\u0027s going on, this is especially true for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s, aggravated when\u00A0they have big payloads. This is a fantastic tool to see dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, and many other extremely useful things:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4635785791\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-12-rcs-build-aid-v091/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I use it in 1.3, don\u0027t remember where I downloaded)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-29T17:42:08Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2017 05:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by kerbalfreak\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Knayder","CreatedById":183167,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T17:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223230879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168054\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221511976872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPart Angle Display is what you are looking for; it\u00A0has been unofficially recompiled for 1.3.1 by linuxgurugamer (see the last post in the thread).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2559952059\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/73551-12x-part-angle-display-including-seamless-highly-accurate-rotation-v0324/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3189839\u0026amp;embedComment=3189839\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:244px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will definetly try this one. I will give a respond when it will be tested \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223230884\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168054\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221511977172\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181766\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbalfreak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, kerbalfreak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4847632497\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127378-131-editor-extensions-redux-released-with-selectroot-merge-stripsymmetry-nooffsetlimits/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Anyway, I don\u0027t see any problem in the picture. You should take a better look at how the center of thrust interacts with the center of mass, wet and dry. With enough control surfaces minor misalignments are not a problem, and with RW and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E in vacuum.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMany players lose the control of the aircraft after spending some fuel and don\u0027t have a clue what\u0027s going on, this is especially true for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s, aggravated when\u00A0they have big payloads. This is a fantastic tool to see dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, and many other extremely useful things:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1808805524\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-12-rcs-build-aid-v091/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I use it in 1.3, don\u0027t remember where I downloaded)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont really have a problem with controlling plane. But plane was still flying little bit up. With \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, everything was ok, but I wanted to have a possibility to fly comfy without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Knayder","CreatedById":183167,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-29T18:29:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea, Part Angle Display works, but it\u0027s not exactly what am I looking for. I can adjust angeling perfectly, but only when I have a part in \u0022hand\u0022. I want to adjust that, when I\u0027m rotating it when it\u0027s placed\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut even with these disadvantages, I was able to manage what I wanted to \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/jYOSRju.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022jYOSRju.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}